Maven Integration
  
  ${df} uses {{{http://maven.apache.org/} Maven}} for managing its projects and dependencies as well as for the build process itself.
  
  Integrating ${df} into projects managed by Maven is simple - all you have to do is declare a corresponding <<<repository>>> element within your project's <<<pom.xml>>> like this:
  
+-----+
<repositories>

  <repository>
    <id>com.anasoft.os.repository.releases</id>
    <name>ANASOFT OpenSource releases</name>
    <url>http://anasoft-os-repo.googlecode.com/svn/repository/releases</url>
  </repository>

  <repository>
    <id>com.anasoft.os.repository.snapshots</id>
    <name>ANASOFT OpenSource snapshots</name>
    <url>http://anasoft-os-repo.googlecode.com/svn/repository/snapshots</url>
  </repository>

</repositories>
+-----+
  
  For most users, declaring the <ANASOFT OpenSource releases> repository is sufficient since it points to stable project releases.
